I completely get Bond fans' concerns over the ending of No Time to Die, but as a dirty casual, I enjoyed the film a lot more than I expected. Glad the fears of school-playish Chibnall Dr Who wokeness were largely unfounded. Good pacing. One or two McGuffin gripes, but trivial.

Well, wrapped up Spectre, great film, and I think I will try and see No Time To Die in theatre. Final thoughts I suppose, Craig was a great bond, Tom Ford makes a mean suit, QoS was the weakest film, but that's not a bad thing, and I prefer the Omega watches to the Rolex ones.
